currentDoc:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

currentSuggestions.original: I think that audiobooks are just as good as reading the actual book.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I think that audiobooks are just as good as reading the actual book.

currentSuggestions.trimmed: audiobooks are so much better than reading books because I love to listen to someone read instead of me reading.
